HEADWORD: outmoded
<hw>outmoded</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>same as
<er>old-fashioned</er>, <pos>a.</pos>, 3.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> antique, demode, old-fashioned{3},
old-hat(predicate), out-of-date, out of fashion(predicate), out of
style(predicate), passe, passee.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Unacceptable because it is inferior to current
standards, procedures, or technology.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> obsolete, outdated, out-of-date, superannuated,
old-fashioned{2}.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Outmost</ent>⟦br⟧
